<p>In the latest development, Israel carried out pre-dawn airstrikes on the Msayleh area in southern Lebanon on Saturday, killing one person, wounding seven, and briefly severing a key highway linking Beirut with the south [thehindu.com#1][npr.org#5][scmp.com#4]. Lebanon’s Health Ministry reported the casualties as strikes hit a site selling heavy machinery, destroying numerous bulldozers and excavators [thehindu.com#1][aljazeera.com#9]. Lebanese President Joseph Aoun condemned the attack as a “heinous” strike against civilian installations, while the Israeli army said it targeted and dismantled Hezbollah infrastructure and engineering machinery used to re-establish it [newarab.com#3][ndtv.com#6]. The raids came a day after a Gaza ceasefire took effect between Hamas and Israel, highlighting a</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/vnhkCqTe0yItOV0EkM_wjgrveb1epr4nIzyiR2knK0kUJlY_8WhEkjUXruTs38UtvHG6nP9dOsVkzm_3-EoO4dZx1iIB1EpZ8a7ZBawKKygNQBZcy26Km_f1JItocTxKbNhcB8_fGhSGp0SefzKQXftS7-aN2uAs6ta_HtA1u5DBR5pG-k5Mjxhkk1QkxxsR2UHlFIrzAQuBsvk' alt='Scene from southern Lebanon following airstrikes in the Msayleh area.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Target and damage: Predawn strikes hit a Msayleh yard selling heavy machinery, destroying many bulldozers and excavators [thehindu.com#1][aljazeera.com#9].</li><li>Casualties, disruption: One person was killed and seven wounded, and the highway linking Beirut to the south was briefly cut [npr.org#5][scmp.com#4].</li><li>Lebanese reaction: President Joseph Aoun condemned the attack as a “heinous” aggression against civilian installations [newarab.com#3][ndtv.com#6].</li><li>Israeli rationale: The Israeli military said it struck and dismantled Hezbollah infrastructure, including engineering machinery used to re-establish it [newarab.com#3].</li><li>Timing context: The strikes occurred a day after a Gaza ceasefire took effect between Hamas and Israel [straitstimes.com#2][scmp.com#4].</li></ul><blockquote>Once again, southern Le